{"key":"processedPost-10733612","value":{"id":10733612,"first":10722008,"last":10737190,"when":1248470174,"utime":"07/25/09 12:16 AM","content":"Coffee and coir are about equal as far as bulk growing goes.&nbsp; Mixed together with verm is a great combination.&nbsp; Those who think the pH of coffee grinds is off are mistaken.&nbsp; Coffee grinds are about a pH 6.5 or so, which is perfect.<br />Oysters grow well on 100% coffee grinds, but cubensis benefits from either manure or coir mixed in with the coffee.&nbsp; If you have coir and verm, mix it with your coffee in about even amounts.&nbsp; Add gypsum at up to ten percent of the amount of coir and coffee for an extra boost.&nbsp; Don't worry about adjusting the pH.&nbsp; It will be in the correct range with those ingredients.<br />RR","title":"Re: A Q on Poop v Coffee"}}